Definition.WordDefinition:
Label \La"bel\, v. t. [imp. & p. p. {Labeled} (l[=a]"b[e^]ld) or {Labelled}; p. pr. & vb. n. {Labeling} or {Labelling}.] 1. To affix a label to; to mark with a name, etc.; as, to label a bottle or a package. [1913 Webster]
2. To affix in or on a label. [R.] [1913 Webster]
labeled adj : bearing or marked with a label or tag; "properly labeled luggage" [syn: {labelled}, {tagged}] [ant: {unlabeled}]
